    "body": "> Hi @gionn, we recently released an alternative to `hardhat-waffle` that has way fewer dependencies. If you are interested, you can learn how to migrate [here](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-runner/docs/guides/migrating-from-hardhat-waffle).\r\n\r\nThat looks cool, I will give a try, thanks for the pointer!\r\n \r\n> Anyway, more generally, the result of `npm audit` tends to be misleading. You can read [this](https://overreacted.io/npm-audit-broken-by-design/) to learn why.\r\n\r\nThanks again, I am a casual npm user and I know that vulnerabilities has different impacts depending on where they are run, but I was more concerned that was a sign of an unmaintained project rather than a critical security risk (even that working on crypto projects made me A LOT more paranoid than before).\r\n\r\n",
